    <stitle>International&#174; MaxxForce&#8482; DT, 9 and 10 Engine Service Manual - Power Cylinders - Installation -
        Piston Rings
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Piston Rings</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>To prevent engine damage, if any piston ring or cylinder sleeve is replaced, replace that cylinder
                    sleeve and piston rings as a set.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3350015483" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figk04/K04004.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil control ring</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil control ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Ring expander coil, paint stripe</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>The orange paint stripe on the ring expander coil must align and show through the oil ring gap.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f3350015484" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh04/H04009.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Piston rings installation (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Make sure the top side of both compression rings (marked with a dot) are facing up. The oil
                    control ring may be installed with either side facing up, if new.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install rings on each piston using a
                <hotlnk document="eges3351_394.xml" xrefid="t335001503">piston ring expander</hotlnk>
                <xref refid="t335001503"/>. Expand the oil control ring enough to fit it over the piston crown and
                install in the lower ring groove of the piston.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Expand the intermediate compression ring and install in the middle piston ring groove.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Expand the top compression ring and install in the top piston ring groove.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
